[[iftags +theme]]
[[module css]]
@import url("https://nu-scptheme.github.io/Black-Highlighter/css/min/normalize.min.css");
@import url("https://nu-scptheme.github.io/Black-Highlighter/css/min/black-highlighter.min.css");

.blbf-main > div.blbf-example::before {
    content: "Example";
}

.blbf-main > div.blbf-intro::before {
    content: "Introduction";
}

.blbf-main > div > p:last-of-type {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
}
[[/module]]

[[include :scp-wiki:component:interwiki-style
| priority=1
| theme=https://nu-scptheme.github.io/Black-Highlighter/css/min/normalize.min.css
]]

[[include :scp-wiki:component:interwiki-style
| priority=2
| theme=https://nu-scptheme.github.io/Black-Highlighter/css/min/black-highlighter.min.css
]]

[[=]]
[[module Rate]]
[[/=]]

----
[[=]]
+++++ This is New Age, a theme made for [[span class="hilighter"]][[[/simulacrum-project-hub|The SIMULACRUM Project]]][[/span]] which is written mostly by [[*user JakdragonX]]. This theme is based off [[[scp-2744|TATTLETALE]]], which is the first article that references **SIMULACRUM**.
[[/=]]
----

[[div class="scp-image-block block-center" style="width:100%;"]]
[[image 	http://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/local--files/theme:new-age/simulacrum-colors.png style="width:100%;" link=#]]
[[div class="scp-image-caption" style="width:100%;"]]
Example of the default New Age theme using numerous colors. Notice that this theme can be configured with 7 total unique colors: ##ff243c|RED##, ##00d142|GREEN##, ##00b8f0|BLUE##, ##36e3b8|TEAL##, ##ff8e14|ORANGE##, ###904ff7|VIOLET##, and ##e165ec|PINK##.
[[/div]]
[[/div]]
@@ @@
[[div class="blbf-main"]]
[[div class="blbf-intro blbf-main-colors"]]
[[div class=".blbf-main > div.blbf-intro::before"]]
[[/div]]
This is a Black Highlighter-based theme, which means you //must// include the Black Highlighter theme on your page in order for New Age to function properly.
> @@[[include :scp-wiki:theme:black-highlighter-theme]]@@
> @@[[include :scp-wiki:theme:new-age]]@@
Red is the default color for this theme. You can also adjust the code above to change the look and feel of the theme. These options include:
> @@[[include :scp-wiki:theme:new-age green/blue/orange/pink/violet/teal=a]]@@
You may also include the "hidetitle" argument to get rid of that pesky article title at the top:
> @@[[include :scp-wiki:theme:black-highlighter-theme]]@@
> @@[[include :scp-wiki:theme:new-age green/blue/orange/pink/violet=a | hidetitle=a]]@@
If you wish to re-color any part of the page using in this theme while also maintaining the current base theme color, you can encapsulate any content using any of the following options:
> @@[[div class="red/green/blue/orange/etc."]]@@
> Place anything you want in here!
> @@[[/div]]@@
Refer below to see extra features and the basic formatting of this article using it's default theme.
[[/div]]
[[/div]]
[[=]]
[[collapsible show="Click me to see some cool stuff!" hide="Glad you enjoyed!" hideLocation="bottom"]]
[[<]]

[[div class="expoblock"]]
[[=]]
+ [[span class="hilighter"]]THIS IS AN EXPOBLOCK.[[/span]]
[[/=]]
----
I completely robbed it from the [[[/theme:isolated-terminal|Isolated Terminal theme]]], which I consider as a favorite theme of mine here on the Wiki. Also notice that the horizontal line is wider as well. To use:
> @@[[div class="expoblock"]]@@
> put your content here or whatever
> @@----@@
> (oh joyous day)
> @@[[/div]]@@

You might've also seen the highlighted text above, which is done using the [[span class="hilighter"]]hilighter[[/span]] span, which I also stole.
> @@[[span class="hilighter"]]text here[[/span]]@@
[[/div]]

[[div class="blbf-main"]]
[[div class="blbf-example blbf-main-colors"]]
[[div class=".blbf-main > div.blbf-example::before"]]
[[/div]]
This is another component I shamelessly robbed, courtesy of [[*user Woedenaz]]'s [[[/component:blacklight-box|Blacklight Box component]]]. Putting a horizontal line in here will also cause it to be wider. **NOTE:** For this component to work on the New Age Theme, you must include it __BEFORE__ you include the actual theme code into your article.

Using this component requires the following code:
> @@[[include :scp-wiki:component:blacklight-box-source |inc-section-start= --]@@
> @@|unique-name=lowercase-nospaces@@
> @@|display-name=text in label@@
> @@]]@@
> Insert content of box here.
> @@[[include :scp-wiki:component:blacklight-box-source |inc-section-end= --]]]@@
[[/div]]
[[/div]]

[[div class="overwatch_notice"]]
[[=]]
++ NOTICE FROM OVERWATCH COMMAND
----
This is a cool label you can use anywhere and that I took from the [[[/theme:basalt|Basalt theme]]] (along with the rest of these divs, sorry). Try it by using the [[span class="hilighter"]]overwatch_notice[[/span]] div.
[[/=]]
[[/div]]

[[div class="green"]]
[[div class="ethics_alert"]]
[[=]]
++ ALERT FROM THE ETHICS COMMITTEE
----
Here's another cool label. Try it with [[span class="hilighter"]]ethics_alert[[/span]]. 
[[/=]]
[[/div]]
[[/div]]

[[div class="blue"]]
[[div class="raisa_update"]]
[[=]]
++ UPDATE FROM THE RECORDS AND INFORMATION SECURITY ADMINISTRATION
----
Are you starting to get the deal? This guy uses [[span class="hilighter"]]raisa_update[[/span]].
[[/=]]
[[/div]]
[[/div]]

[[div class="teal"]]
[[div class="classification_warning"]]
[[=]]
++ INCOMING WARNING FROM THE CLASSIFICATION COMMITTEE
----
Here's another in case you weren't. Try this one with [[span class="hilighter"]]classification_warning[[/span]]. 
[[/=]]
[[/div]]
[[/div]]

[[div class="orange"]]
[[div class="miscom_message"]]
[[=]]
++ MESSAGE FROM THE DEPARTMENT OF MISCOMMUNICATIONS
----
And the final one. This one uses [[span class="hilighter"]]miscom_message[[/span]].
[[/=]]
[[/div]]
[[/div]]
[[div class="modal"]]
This is also a basic modal, taken again from Basalt (sorry [[*user Liryn]] and [[*user Placeholder McD]]). You can use it by:
> @@[[div class="modal"]]@@
> cool content or whatever.
> @@[[/div]]@@
[[/div]]

[[div class="smallmodal"]]
This is the same as above, but smaller. Try it by using:
> @@[[div class="smallmodal"]]@@
> I'm getting sick of writing these.
> @@[[/div]]@@
[[/div]]

[[div class="blockquote"]]
This theme also ports from [[[/theme:penumbra-bhl|Penumbra BHL]]] (which means I also stole entirely from it) to allow the usage of sideblocks on this theme. Using them is just like using them on Penumbra BHL:
[[div class="blockquote"]]
@@[[div class="limit"]]@@ <-- Set the start limit of the anchor
@@[[div class="anchor"]]@@ <-- Set sidebox's sticky position
@@[[div class="sidebox"]]@@
Some sidebox text here.
@@[[/div]]@@
@@[[/div]]@@

Text where sidebox scroll past.

@@[[/div]]@@ <-- Set the end limit of the anchor
[[/div]]
[[/div]]
[[/<]]
[[/collapsible]]
[[/=]]
+ Examples

